    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-22T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-22T22:00:00-05:00" n="123"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.24/147b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-22T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 22, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Military equipment for 5,000 men has been approved. Plans for shipment now
                    being worked out. Military radio equipment critical <pb facs="0128" n="116"
                        xml:id="pg_116"/> and cannot be supplied at present. Finger<note n="45"
                        xml:id="d123fn45">John W. Finger, who had been engaged by the Ethiopian
                        Government to assist on lend-lease aid, etc.</note> and Anis are consulting
                    with appropriate agencies in regard to transport planes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
